\title{Skill Finder Verifier}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Find locally-created skills and verify provenance. Distinguishes locally-created from batch-installed by diffing against asi/skills/ baseline. Evaluates modified downloads for functional improvement. Triggers: new skills, local skills, skill audit, skill provenance, skill verification.}

\subtree{
\title{Skill Finder & Verifier}
\p{Script: \code{\startverbpython3 /Users/alice/.claude/skills/skill-finder-verifier/scripts/finder.py\stopverb} Baseline: \code{\startverb/Users/alice/v/asi/skills/\stopverb} (upstream plurigrid/asi)}

\subtree{
\title{Operations}
\pre{\startverb
# Scan all directories, classify every skill
python3 scripts/finder.py scan

# Scan a single location (agents|claude|codex|goose|copilot|openhands)
python3 scripts/finder.py scan claude

# Verify a specific skill's provenance
python3 scripts/finder.py verify ducklake

# Show diff between local and asi version
python3 scripts/finder.py diff boris
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Classification}
\ul{
\li{\strong{local-only}: Not in asi/skills/ at all. Genuinely created here.}
\li{\strong{modified}: Exists in asi but SKILL.md differs. Candidate for "functionally better" evaluation.}
\li{\strong{identical}: Same hash as asi. Batch-installed, unmodified.}
\li{\strong{identical-md-extra-files}: SKILL.md matches but local has additional files (scripts, assets).}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Evaluating Modified Skills}
\p{When a skill is classified as \strong{modified}, evaluate whether the changes make it functionally better by loading these 5 skills:}

\ol{
\li{\strong{sharp-edges} — Does the modified version fix footgun designs or dangerous defaults?}
\li{\strong{refuse-mediocrity} — Does it raise the quality bar vs the generic upstream?}
\li{\strong{code-review} — Are any added scripts well-written and correct?}
\li{\strong{hogwash-removal} — Does it strip filler and add substance?}
\li{\strong{skill-validation-gf3} — Does it maintain valid skill structure?}
}

\p{A modified skill counts as "functionally better" when it meets \strong{3+ of 5} evaluator criteria:}

\ul{
\li{Adds environment-specific instructions the upstream lacks}
\li{Includes working scripts/assets the upstream doesn't have}
\li{Fixes incorrect or misleading guidance}
\li{Removes generic filler, adds grounded instructions}
\li{Maintains valid SKILL.md structure with proper frontmatter}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{What This Skill Is NOT}
\p{Not a batch installer. Not for downloading skills. Only for finding what's already here and verifying its provenance.}
}
}